              <div class="space-y-3" id="faq">
                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md">
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="w-full text-left px-4 py-3 flex justify-between items-center faq-question"
                  >
                    <span class="font-medium text-gray-800"
                      >How do you do unit conversions in math?</span
                    >
                    <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">+</span>
                  </button>
                  <div
                    class="px-4 pb-3 hidden faq-answer text-sm text-gray-700"
                  >
                    The most reliable method is dimensional analysis
                    (factor‑label). Write the given value with its unit,
                    multiply by one or more conversion factors written as
                    fractions that equal 1 (for example 1 in / 2.54 cm), and
                    cancel units until only the desired unit remains. This
                    method works for simple one‑step conversions and complex
                    multi‑step problems alike.
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md">
                  <button
                    type="button"
