                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md">
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="w-full text-left px-4 py-3 flex justify-between items-center faq-question"
                  >
                    <span class="font-medium text-gray-800"
                      >How can I check if my conversion answer is
                      reasonable?</span
                    >
                    <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">+</span>
                  </button>
                  <div
                    class="px-4 pb-3 hidden faq-answer text-sm text-gray-700"
                  >
                    Use estimation and intuition. For example, 1 inch is about
                    2.5 cm, so 10 inches should be about 25 cm, not 2.5 cm or
                    250 cm. When converting from a larger unit to a smaller unit
                    (meters to centimeters), the number should get bigger. When
                    converting from a smaller unit to a larger unit (seconds to
                    hours), the number should get smaller. If your answer goes
                    in the wrong direction, recheck your conversion factor.
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md">
