                    significant figures in the given data. For example, if a
                    length is given as 3.20 m (three significant figures), your
                    converted value should also have about three significant
                    figures. Exact definitions like 1 inch = exactly 2.54 cm can
                    be treated as having infinite precision, so they do not
                    limit the significant figures.
                  </div>
